---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';

// Import images
import portraitPinkDesk from '../assets/portrait-pink-desk.jpg';
import portraitPinkHandUp from '../assets/portrait-pink-hand-up.jpg';
import speakingApiConf24 from '../assets/speaking-apiconf24.png';
---

<Layout 
  title="Motunrayo Koyejo | Engineer, Creator, Speaker, Mentor" 
  currentPage="index"
>
  <header style="padding: 90px 0 40px;">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="eyebrow">Engineer · Creator · Speaker · Mentor</div>
      <h1>Hi, I'm Motunrayo, and I build the <em>quiet</em> systems that keep fintech running.</h1>
      <p class="lede">By day, I'm a backend engineer shaping payment and investment infrastructure across Africa. By evening, I'm somewhere else entirely: on a conference stage, recording a TikTok, or on a call with a mentee trying to land her first engineering role. This little corner of the internet is where all of that lives.</p>
      <div class="hero-photo" style="background-image: url('/headshot-mint.jpg'); background-position: center 30%;"></div>
      <div class="scroll-hint">keep scrolling, there's more</div>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="recognition">
      <div class="recognition-grid">
        <div>
          <div class="stat-num">Top 50</div>
          <div class="stat-label">Named a Women Tech Titan in Nigeria, 2026</div>
        </div>
        <div>
          <div class="stat-num">20+</div>
          <div class="stat-label">Conference talks across Africa and beyond</div>
        </div>
        <div>
          <div class="stat-num">40+</div>
          <div class="stat-label">Women mentored into their first tech roles</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Pillar: Work -->
  <section style="padding: 0;">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="pillar">
        <div class="pillar-copy">
          <div class="section-label">Work</div>
          <h2>Backend engineering, in <em>fintech</em>.</h2>
          <p>My work sits where software, money, and scale meet.</p>
          <p>I've spent the last six years building and improving the systems that power financial products, from payment infrastructure and banking integrations to investment platforms and market expansion initiatives. I enjoy turning complex operational challenges into reliable systems that customers can trust.</p>
          <a class="pillar-link" href="/work">See what I've built →</a>
        </div>
        <div class="photo ratio-3-4">
          <Image
            src={portraitPinkDesk}
            alt="Motunrayo at her desk"
            style="object-position: center 30%;"
          />
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="pillar reverse">
        <div class="pillar-copy">
          <div class="section-label">Creator</div>
          <h2>Making tech feel <em>less scary</em>, one video at a time.</h2>
          <p>A few years into my career, I realised the stuff I'd figured out (how to actually read a codebase, how to prep for an interview without panicking, what a day in a backend engineer's life looks like) wasn't being explained anywhere a beginner
          could find it. So I started making videos. Now I do it on YouTube and TikTok, mostly because I enjoy it.</p>
          <a class="pillar-link" href="/videos">Come watch with me →</a>
        </div>
        <div class="photo ratio-3-4">
          <Image
            src={portraitPinkHandUp}
            alt="Motunrayo portrait with hand up"
            style="object-position: center 25%;"
          />
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="pillar">
        <div class="pillar-copy">
          <div class="section-label">Speaking</div>
          <h2>On stage, <em>sharing what I've learned</em>.</h2>
          <p>I've spent my career building products used by millions of people, and speaking gives me a chance to share the lessons behind that work.</p>
          <p>Over the years, I've spoken to engineers, founders, and students about backend engineering, fintech, APIs, career growth, and the realities of building technology in Africa. I enjoy breaking down complex ideas into stories and lessons people can immediately apply.</p>
          <a class="pillar-link" href="/speaking">See where I've been →</a>
        </div>
        <div class="hero-photo" style="aspect-ratio: 4/3;"></div>
      </div>

      <div class="pillar reverse">
        <div class="pillar-copy">
          <div class="section-label">Mentoring</div>
          <h2>Holding the door <em>open</em>.</h2>
          <p>When I started out, I spent years trying to answer questions that seem obvious now:</p>
          <p><em>Am I good enough? What should I learn next? How do I get my first opportunity?</em></p>
          <p>I didn't always have someone to ask.</p>
          <p>I care so deeply about mentoring women in technology. I enjoy helping early-career engineers navigate the uncertainty that comes with starting out, whether that's technical growth, career direction, interviewing, or simply building confidence.</p>
          <a class="pillar-link" href="/mentoring">Learn about my mentoring →</a>
        </div>
        <div class="photo ratio-3-4">
          <Image
            src={speakingApiConf24}
            alt="Motunrayo speaking at API Conference 2024"
            style="object-position: center 20%;"
          />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
